WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.650 --> 00:00:06.837
As I said at the beginning of Mass,
today we celebrate Saint Joseph.

00:00:06.837 --> 00:00:12.424
I’m sure many of you have a
devotion to him; I’m sure you also

00:00:12.424 --> 00:00:14.020
have experiences—testimonies—of
his intercession.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:19.607
But today, in this homily and reflection
on the Gospel, I would rather that

00:00:19.607 --> 00:00:24.795
we come to understand a little
better Joseph’s role, and the part he

00:00:24.795 --> 00:00:27.190
played in the history of salvation.

00:00:27.965 --> 00:00:33.671
That’s why, when you read the
Gospels, the evangelists make a real

00:00:33.671 --> 00:00:39.853
effort to emphasise that Joseph is
by origin from the house of David.

00:00:39.853 --> 00:00:46.511
And then you’ll see in Luke’s Gospel it’s
mentioned six times, in Matthew’s four

00:00:46.511 --> 00:00:53.645
times, and it’s very important to them
to stress that Joseph is of David’s line.

00:00:53.645 --> 00:00:59.351
And if you listened carefully to
the Gospel… in the first sentence

00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:02.205
it said: Joseph, son of Jacob.

00:01:02.845 --> 00:01:08.497
Now we have “Joseph, son of Jacob”,
and then the Gospel ends with the

00:01:08.497 --> 00:01:13.342
angel appearing and saying, “Joseph,
son of David.” So the angel himself

00:01:13.342 --> 00:01:18.590
confirms that Joseph is of Davidic
origin, of the royal line of David.

00:01:18.590 --> 00:01:23.839
Even though the Gospel says “son
of Jacob” right at the start, in

00:01:23.839 --> 00:01:28.683
the very first sentence, the angel
stresses at the annunciation who he

00:01:28.683 --> 00:01:34.740
is: that he is a son of David. You
can see that in Matthew’s Gospel.

00:01:36.900 --> 00:01:43.529
Why was it so important to
emphasise that Jesus – and Joseph

00:01:43.529 --> 00:01:46.542
too – were of Davidic descent?

00:01:46.542 --> 00:01:54.377
Because… if we read the Old Testament,
we’ll see that the last great

00:01:54.377 --> 00:02:01.007
bond God made, the last covenants
He established, were with whom?

00:02:01.007 --> 00:02:02.212
With David.

00:02:02.212 --> 00:02:10.047
He made them with David because the
Jewish people were expecting that chosen

00:02:10.047 --> 00:02:18.484
one, that Messiah, who would establish
a kingdom, who would set His people free

00:02:18.484 --> 00:02:23.306
and who, it says, would build the Temple.

00:02:23.306 --> 00:02:32.346
But perhaps most important of all: that
He and the Father would be one, that

00:02:32.346 --> 00:02:36.565
they would love one another so deeply.

00:02:36.565 --> 00:02:40.838
And in the first reading we
heard, in 1 Samuel, that this

00:02:40.838 --> 00:02:42.262
was expected in prophecy.

00:02:42.262 --> 00:02:47.248
So that future king was meant to fulfil
those conditions: to establish a kingdom,

00:02:47.248 --> 00:02:52.946
to build the Temple, to set the people
free – but most important of all, the sign

00:02:52.946 --> 00:02:58.643
by which they would recognise him: that
he and the Son, the Son and the Father,

00:02:58.643 --> 00:03:01.136
are one, that they love one another.

00:03:01.136 --> 00:03:06.478
However, as we go on in the Old Testament,
we’ll see that God didn’t really

00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:08.615
want David to establish the kingdom.

00:03:09.155 --> 00:03:11.630
But his son, Solomon, would.

00:03:11.630 --> 00:03:18.068
Yet David, as a true and good father
and king—devout and faithful to

00:03:18.068 --> 00:03:24.010
the Law—did his utmost, and when
you read the Old Testament you’ll

00:03:24.010 --> 00:03:29.457
see that he practically prepared
everything so that his son Solomon

00:03:29.457 --> 00:03:32.428
could build the Temple in Jerusalem.

00:03:32.428 --> 00:03:39.361
In fact, in the Old Testament you have
a detailed description of the materials

00:03:39.361 --> 00:03:46.788
King David set aside for his son,
so that he could build the Temple in

00:03:46.788 --> 00:03:49.760
Jerusalem more easily and more quickly.

00:03:49.760 --> 00:03:53.530
So it describes there the
timber, the materials.

00:03:53.530 --> 00:04:01.072
But it wasn’t granted to him, even
though he was so close to God, it wasn’t

00:04:01.072 --> 00:04:04.372
granted to him to build the Temple.

00:04:04.372 --> 00:04:10.971
Rather, that task was meant to be—
it was entrusted to his son Solomon.

00:04:10.971 --> 00:04:12.856
But what’s the problem?

00:04:12.856 --> 00:04:18.984
Although God wanted Solomon, David’s
son, to build that Temple, from what I

00:04:18.984 --> 00:04:25.583
said about the prophecies that that king
was meant to have, Solomon didn’t have

00:04:25.583 --> 00:04:32.183
one— and perhaps the most important: he
didn’t have a close relationship with God.

00:04:32.183 --> 00:04:37.368
Even though he had the preparations,
and the building materials for

00:04:37.368 --> 00:04:43.495
constructing the Temple, even though he
was given that trust and became king,

00:04:43.495 --> 00:04:50.095
he didn’t have a close relationship
with God, and then it all fell apart.

00:04:50.615 --> 00:04:52.305
And everything fell apart.

00:04:52.305 --> 00:04:57.377
And of course the people then went
into crisis, asking themselves whether

00:04:57.377 --> 00:05:02.449
that prophecy—that the Messiah would
come from the line of David—had already

00:05:02.449 --> 00:05:08.788
been fulfilled and he had already come,
or whether he was still yet to come.

00:05:08.788 --> 00:05:13.860
However, with the birth of Jesus,
the Jews began to realise that

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:18.087
part of those prophecies had been
fulfilled—partly, but not completely.

00:05:18.087 --> 00:05:23.581
And so some believed that one
part of it, the promises, had been

00:05:23.581 --> 00:05:25.695
fulfilled, and others did not.

00:05:26.245 --> 00:05:31.234
And that’s why the evangelists
place such emphasis on Joseph’s

00:05:31.234 --> 00:05:38.220
lineage, and why the angel says
that he is of the line of David.

00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:44.707
That’s why, when you read the Gospel
– especially Matthew 1:1 – you get those

00:05:44.707 --> 00:05:50.694
opening genealogies, where we sometimes
rather quickly lose track once we start

00:05:50.694 --> 00:05:54.686
listening: so-and-so fathered so-and-so,
and so-and-so fathered so-and-so.

00:05:54.686 --> 00:06:01.173
But in the Gospel, Matthew is trying to
underline precisely Jesus’ royal ancestry:

00:06:01.173 --> 00:06:05.165
that he comes from the line of David.

00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:10.645
That he comes out of that prophecy:
that a Messiah was to come, the one

00:06:10.645 --> 00:06:15.395
who would build a temple that cannot
be destroyed, who would unite the

00:06:15.395 --> 00:06:19.414
people, but most importantly, who
would be united with the Father.

00:06:19.414 --> 00:06:24.163
And that is why, in the birth of
Jesus, and in Matthew’s Gospel,

00:06:24.163 --> 00:06:27.817
the other evangelists emphasise
this very, very strongly: that the

00:06:27.817 --> 00:06:30.375
Gospel is, after all, the Good News.

00:06:30.375 --> 00:06:36.112
So that this prophecy hasn’t
been lost, but that it is

00:06:36.112 --> 00:06:38.198
actually happening right now.

00:06:38.198 --> 00:06:40.285
Now, what’s important here?

00:06:40.285 --> 00:06:43.414
So, Joseph—look, Jesus has been born.

00:06:49.485 --> 00:06:57.261
And now we come to what’s important
about Joseph’s and Jesus’ origins.

00:06:57.261 --> 00:07:04.390
So Joseph and Jesus aren’t
of the royal family by blood.

00:07:04.390 --> 00:07:13.464
And what mattered for inheritance in the
Old Testament was the law, not biology.

00:07:13.464 --> 00:07:21.241
And by the law, since they fulfilled
it, David, Salmon, Joseph and

00:07:21.241 --> 00:07:25.777
Jesus all come from the royal line.

00:07:25.777 --> 00:07:32.906
At Christmas we always have
this image of the manger, of

00:07:32.906 --> 00:07:36.795
poor little Jesus, but he isn’t.

00:07:36.795 --> 00:07:42.961
It’s true he was born in a
stable, but he isn’t a nobody.

00:07:42.961 --> 00:07:48.653
He is of royal lineage, the
future king who will establish an

00:07:48.653 --> 00:07:51.499
indestructible temple and be a priest.

00:07:51.499 --> 00:07:58.140
And that’s what’s important to emphasise:
Joseph is a member of the royal family

00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:01.461
precisely through the keeping of the Law.

00:08:01.461 --> 00:08:07.153
Let’s go back again to the Old
Testament, so we can better

00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:09.525
understand some of these comparisons.

00:08:11.175 --> 00:08:18.875
In theology, that Solomon, who had the
duty to build it all, that prophecy, that

00:08:18.875 --> 00:08:26.061
image he was meant to create, is often
compared, of course, with Jesus’ kingdom.

00:08:26.061 --> 00:08:34.788
And at that time, the temple was meant to
be built: Solomon was to build a temple.

00:08:34.788 --> 00:08:40.434
He had twelve governors, a kind
of administration of the temple

00:08:40.434 --> 00:08:47.108
and the kingdom, and in the temple
there were to be offered precisely

00:08:47.108 --> 00:08:49.675
unbloody sacrifices: bread and wine.

00:08:49.675 --> 00:08:55.023
And that is exactly what it
meant in Greek: the Eucharist.

00:08:55.023 --> 00:09:02.315
Now, you see, David was not allowed
to build that temple, but his son was.

00:09:02.315 --> 00:09:09.122
Yet because he was not faithful to God,
because he was not closely connected

00:09:09.122 --> 00:09:13.012
with Him, it never actually came to pass.

00:09:13.012 --> 00:09:18.846
But if we look at the analogy
of these events, we’ll notice

00:09:18.846 --> 00:09:20.305
something rather striking.

00:09:21.485 --> 00:09:27.766
We say of Joseph that he was a carpenter,
and even—let’s put it in simpler terms to

00:09:27.766 --> 00:09:30.722
sum up all those trades—he was a builder.

00:09:30.722 --> 00:09:35.157
Most likely Joseph, as a construction
worker, would have had certain materials.

00:09:35.157 --> 00:09:39.221
He would certainly have had
wood if he was a carpenter.

00:09:39.221 --> 00:09:44.395
He would certainly have had some sort
of workshop where he made those things.

00:09:45.175 --> 00:09:52.640
And now we have King David, who prepared
everything for his son – all the materials

00:09:52.640 --> 00:09:55.626
– for the building of that temple.

00:09:55.626 --> 00:10:01.599
I believe Joseph likewise had something
he left to Jesus: an inheritance,

00:10:01.599 --> 00:10:08.069
just as David left what was needed
for the building of that temple.

00:10:08.069 --> 00:10:12.548
King David had his mother,
whose name was Bathsheba.

00:10:12.548 --> 00:10:19.019
He brought her into the royal
court so that she could be his

00:10:19.019 --> 00:10:21.010
adviser in certain situations.

00:10:21.610 --> 00:10:27.694
Jesus takes Mary with him,
and in a way Joseph, too.

00:10:27.694 --> 00:10:34.332
On the Cross, when Jesus died,
he left us his mother Mary,

00:10:34.332 --> 00:10:37.098
just as David had Bathsheba.

00:10:37.098 --> 00:10:44.290
On the other side of this prophetic
comparison, we see that, just as

00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:50.928
David brought Bathsheba into his own
household and into the royal court,

00:10:50.928 --> 00:10:55.353
so Jesus leaves his mother Mary to us.

00:10:55.353 --> 00:11:02.544
It’s interesting to see how that
prophecy, which was meant to be fulfilled

00:11:02.544 --> 00:11:09.182
in the Old Testament, was established
along that same royal line precisely

00:11:09.182 --> 00:11:16.374
thanks to Joseph, who accepted God’s
family, so that God might build what

00:11:16.374 --> 00:11:19.140
matters most: the indestructible temple.

00:11:19.925 --> 00:11:23.434
All of us, Scripture says, are
temples of the Holy Spirit.

00:11:23.434 --> 00:11:25.667
And together we make up one temple.

00:11:25.667 --> 00:11:28.538
No matter that we’re scattered
across different cities, no

00:11:28.538 --> 00:11:32.367
matter if this basilica were to
collapse, we are the living Church.

00:11:32.367 --> 00:11:37.152
You know, I say here that the saddest
thing is to see a beautiful church

00:11:37.152 --> 00:11:39.067
building with no people in it.

00:11:39.067 --> 00:11:42.895
It’s better to celebrate Mass
on a sports stadium pitch with a

00:11:42.895 --> 00:11:46.405
hundred people than in some empty
basilica, wherever it may be.

00:11:47.045 --> 00:11:49.246
So we are the living Church.

00:11:49.246 --> 00:11:54.015
And that is what God wanted: that an
indestructible temple should be built.

00:11:54.015 --> 00:11:56.216
And that is what Jesus did.

00:11:56.216 --> 00:12:01.352
First he allowed his body, as the
temple, to be destroyed, and he rose

00:12:01.352 --> 00:12:06.121
again on the third day; and from
then on the living Church exists.

00:12:06.121 --> 00:12:07.955
We, the limbs of Christ.

00:12:07.955 --> 00:12:11.990
We who, through baptism, have
been grafted into him, and who

00:12:11.990 --> 00:12:13.824
are, in a way, indestructible.

00:12:15.090 --> 00:12:21.866
All of us today, when we reflect
on Saint Joseph and his role, we

00:12:21.866 --> 00:12:24.770
all need both Joseph and Mary.

00:12:24.770 --> 00:12:30.578
What is beautifully highlighted—and where
Solomon failed—is this: if I bring out

00:12:30.578 --> 00:12:37.354
the Gospel and read the sentence again,
you would see that prophecy, how many

00:12:37.354 --> 00:12:44.614
times Jesus says, “I and the Father are
one.” And in the first reading, that

00:12:44.614 --> 00:12:51.875
is exactly what was asked of David’s
son, Solomon, and he did not keep it.

00:12:51.875 --> 00:12:54.178
He was not one with the Father.

00:12:54.178 --> 00:12:59.116
And Jesus always stresses that communion:
“I and the Father are one.” So we already

00:12:59.116 --> 00:13:03.394
have prophecy fulfilled; we have the
temple of God established, one that can

00:13:03.394 --> 00:13:08.331
no longer be brought down. And we already
know it has endured for 2,000 years.

00:13:08.331 --> 00:13:13.268
Jesus says, “Not even the gates of hell
will prevail against it.” We have the

00:13:13.268 --> 00:13:17.876
communion of the Father and the Son;
we have the Holy Spirit who, through

00:13:17.876 --> 00:13:20.510
baptism, has grafted us into all of that.

00:13:20.970 --> 00:13:25.376
And what’s interesting is
that Joseph’s role was to look

00:13:25.376 --> 00:13:28.020
after and care for that family.

00:13:28.020 --> 00:13:32.867
But do we need Joseph today,
do we need Mary today?

00:13:32.867 --> 00:13:34.630
Do we need them?

00:13:38.045 --> 00:13:44.844
I believe you’ve heard it – you’re
young, but you may still have heard your

00:13:44.844 --> 00:13:50.186
parents say about someone else, “I’ve
provided everything for him.” Parents

00:13:50.186 --> 00:13:56.015
often say that: “I’ve provided everything
for him, I’ve given him everything.”

00:13:56.015 --> 00:14:02.814
You see, what is it, then, that parents
may sometimes have forgotten to give?

00:14:02.814 --> 00:14:09.613
What is it… what did David – such an
outstanding father, steeped in wisdom, a

00:14:09.613 --> 00:14:13.984
man of God – fail to give his son Solomon?

00:14:15.704 --> 00:14:22.288
What is it that so many parents today
fail to give their children, and then,

00:14:22.288 --> 00:14:27.995
in quotes, they say, “I’ve provided
everything for my child, I’ve given my

00:14:27.995 --> 00:14:34.140
child everything”? What was it that Joseph
could give to Jesus? Even though Jesus

00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:37.212
didn’t need it, because Jesus is God.

00:14:37.212 --> 00:14:40.723
And do you know what he gave him?

00:14:40.723 --> 00:14:43.357
He gave him a virtuous life.

00:14:43.357 --> 00:14:46.430
That’s where David went
wrong with Solomon.

00:14:46.730 --> 00:14:50.880
That’s why he didn’t fulfil God’s
prophecy and wasn’t one with the

00:14:50.880 --> 00:14:55.376
Father as Jesus was, because in
a way he drifted away from God.

00:14:55.376 --> 00:15:00.563
What good is it today if you give your
child everything, and they’ve moved away

00:15:00.563 --> 00:15:05.059
from God—then they go off the rails, start
taking drugs, drinking, partying, driving

00:15:05.059 --> 00:15:09.210
ridiculously expensive cars, killing
other people, and so on, and so on.

00:15:09.210 --> 00:15:14.035
And then you asked yourself, “Where
did I make that mistake in bringing

00:15:14.035 --> 00:15:18.860
them up?” Well, here’s where you
made it. You didn’t give them virtue.

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:21.830
You didn’t teach them,
in their upbringing, to…

00:15:24.375 --> 00:15:29.933
He engraves it into himself, to accept the
virtues and the graces of the Holy Spirit.

00:15:29.933 --> 00:15:35.144
That’s what I believe so many of our
young people are lacking: a virtuous life.

00:15:35.144 --> 00:15:40.355
And I’m saying, Joseph certainly knew how
to give that to Jesus — even though Jesus

00:15:40.355 --> 00:15:43.135
didn’t need it — but we need it today.

00:15:43.135 --> 00:15:48.825
That’s why I asked the question: what are
we going to learn from Joseph today, apart

00:15:48.825 --> 00:15:51.670
from just pestering him for our own needs?

00:15:51.670 --> 00:15:56.650
Before we start pestering him with our
needs, let’s ask: is our life virtuous?

00:15:56.650 --> 00:16:00.562
Those of you who are older and
have children—are you teaching

00:16:00.562 --> 00:16:02.340
your children to live virtuously?

00:16:02.340 --> 00:16:05.541
That’s an important message
for all of us today.

00:16:05.541 --> 00:16:10.876
And I’d really like us to stop treating
Saint Joseph the way we do Saint

00:16:10.876 --> 00:16:15.500
Anthony—just using him as a means to
an end and telling little stories.

00:16:15.710 --> 00:16:20.736
Of course these are tremendous
testimonies, and they’re such great saints

00:16:20.736 --> 00:16:23.021
who are, naturally, our intercessors.

00:16:23.021 --> 00:16:28.048
But sometimes I get the feeling
that with certain things we

00:16:28.048 --> 00:16:30.790
end up being a bit superficial.

00:16:30.790 --> 00:16:35.360
We’ve just explained that
Joseph is of a royal family.

00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:38.559
Jesus too is of a royal family.

00:16:38.559 --> 00:16:40.387
That’s a big thing.

00:16:40.387 --> 00:16:46.785
We are baptised, and then we have
no right to say that we’re not

00:16:46.785 --> 00:16:49.069
somebody, that we’re not important.

00:16:49.209 --> 00:16:53.589
Yes, because we too are baptised,
part of the royal family.

00:16:53.589 --> 00:16:55.181
Do you understand that?

00:16:55.181 --> 00:17:01.152
So we are part of this story as well,
because you are grafted into Jesus.

00:17:01.152 --> 00:17:06.327
And what’s interesting about Saint
Joseph, what we can see, is that even

00:17:06.327 --> 00:17:12.697
if he knew he was of royal lineage, he
lived humbly, he lived in poverty, he

00:17:12.697 --> 00:17:15.085
lived in silence, quietly, without fuss.

00:17:15.085 --> 00:17:19.464
He knew how to live out
that royal dignity of his.

00:17:19.825 --> 00:17:25.057
That would be wonderful if we Christians
knew how, in the silence of our hearts,

00:17:25.057 --> 00:17:29.592
to carry that pride and live out
the dignity of being God’s children.

00:17:29.592 --> 00:17:34.475
No matter what anyone thinks of me,
how others see me, I am somebody;

00:17:34.475 --> 00:17:36.917
I’m not an accident in this world.

00:17:36.917 --> 00:17:41.801
I am part of a royal family; someone
paid dearly for me with blood.

00:17:41.801 --> 00:17:45.289
Someone planned this whole history,
the history of the ages—through

00:17:45.289 --> 00:17:48.777
the prophets, through the inspired
words of the evangelists—right up

00:17:48.777 --> 00:17:54.010
to Jesus, so that today I could
be a member, a part of that story.

00:17:54.250 --> 00:18:00.201
And we ought to be happy; all
of us here should, right now,

00:18:00.201 --> 00:18:02.490
have crowns on our heads.

00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:04.321
Not bishops’ mitres—royal ones.

00:18:04.321 --> 00:18:06.611
Don’t think I’m going mad.

00:18:06.611 --> 00:18:13.478
I’ve said I’d turn down a bishop’s post
because of my hairstyle, so don’t worry.

00:18:13.478 --> 00:18:18.056
What matters is that we
actually feel that way too.

00:18:18.056 --> 00:18:24.465
And especially for men: Saint Joseph
is both a protector and the one who

00:18:24.465 --> 00:18:26.755
inspires, helps, and gives strength.

00:18:26.755 --> 00:18:31.548
However, what stands out about Saint
Joseph is his silence: he didn’t

00:18:31.548 --> 00:18:36.740
lead noisily, and in that silence
he was able to hear God’s voice.

00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:41.134
Just imagine that situation: an
angel appears to you and gives

00:18:41.134 --> 00:18:47.126
you such a huge task — that you
are to care for the Son of God.

00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:49.123
Of course he was confused.

00:18:49.123 --> 00:18:54.715
Come on, lads, how many of you have
found yourselves in that kind of

00:18:54.715 --> 00:18:59.508
situation — how many times have you
had difficult decisions in life, when

00:18:59.508 --> 00:19:02.304
you were afraid and confused as well?

00:19:04.590 --> 00:19:07.980
And of course, if you’re making
serious decisions, or if God has

00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:11.652
entrusted you with a task — and
especially you who are going to get

00:19:11.652 --> 00:19:15.607
married, and you who are already
married — you have to take up your role.

00:19:15.607 --> 00:19:18.150
Do you know how sad and tragic it is?

00:19:18.150 --> 00:19:23.235
When I say a man should take up his role,
I don’t mean he should be some brute.

00:19:23.235 --> 00:19:27.190
Because the Gospel says that the man
should be the head of the family.

00:19:27.690 --> 00:19:29.146
Unfortunately, sometimes
men misunderstand that.

00:19:29.146 --> 00:19:33.226
It doesn’t mean being the head of
the family so you can bully others

00:19:33.226 --> 00:19:35.266
and be the boss of the house.

00:19:35.266 --> 00:19:36.140
No — the opposite.

00:19:36.140 --> 00:19:36.723
The opposite.

00:19:36.723 --> 00:19:40.802
If we look at the life of Saint
Joseph, and if he’s been given

00:19:40.802 --> 00:19:44.882
to men as a model, then the first
thing he does is in silence.

00:19:44.882 --> 00:19:48.670
First, he doesn’t listen to his wife
or the child — he doesn’t listen

00:19:48.670 --> 00:19:50.710
to his wife or the child first.

00:19:51.210 --> 00:19:52.277
Constantly with God.

00:19:52.277 --> 00:19:54.412
Now get up, now set off.

00:19:54.412 --> 00:19:56.546
Now go there, now go here.

00:19:56.546 --> 00:20:01.171
That’s what men need: to calm down
a bit and, whatever decisions and

00:20:01.171 --> 00:20:06.152
whatever awaits you in life, first
to stop with God, to have a word

00:20:06.152 --> 00:20:11.845
with him, to hear where he’s sending
you, what you need to do, and to have

00:20:11.845 --> 00:20:15.047
that trust in God—to be a man of God.

00:20:15.047 --> 00:20:20.384
And you know how that then shows itself
in the family, towards the other members

00:20:20.384 --> 00:20:25.009
of the family, towards your wife and
towards your children: because then you

00:20:25.009 --> 00:20:30.701
have to be an authority—on the one hand
a firm rock, and on the other hand,

00:20:30.701 --> 00:20:32.125
gentleness, kindness, and goodness.

00:20:33.565 --> 00:20:36.472
But you’ve got to be the one
who takes the initiative.

00:20:36.472 --> 00:20:37.529
The one who leads.

00:20:37.529 --> 00:20:40.437
It’s sad today, seeing how
many men have lost their way.

00:20:40.437 --> 00:20:43.080
They don’t know where they’re
going, or who’s leading them.

00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:46.781
When the woman has to be the one making
the decisions at home—what’s going

00:20:46.781 --> 00:20:48.895
to happen and how it’s going to be.

00:20:48.895 --> 00:20:51.803
This has nothing to do with the
feminist movement; I’m saying

00:20:51.803 --> 00:20:53.125
everything’s got completely muddled up.

00:20:53.784 --> 00:20:59.541
So I don’t really know any more what’s
what with the family — chaos, chaos.

00:20:59.541 --> 00:21:05.710
But I’ve got this feeling, and it’s a
good thing, that I’m noticing you young

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:08.177
people are searching for that identity.

00:21:08.177 --> 00:21:11.055
Look, a brilliant example is Saint Joseph.

00:21:11.055 --> 00:21:11.466
Brilliant.

00:21:11.466 --> 00:21:17.223
Believe me, you won’t lose any part
of yourself if you become a bit

00:21:17.223 --> 00:21:19.691
quieter, and act from inner strength.

00:21:19.691 --> 00:21:24.625
Because if you’re in a relationship
with God, you gain that inner

00:21:24.625 --> 00:21:29.560
confidence — and your girlfriend,
and your wife, will feel it in you.

00:21:30.200 --> 00:21:34.265
When a man doesn’t have that
inner confidence, it’s a disaster.

00:21:34.265 --> 00:21:38.331
Then everyone’s disorientated: him, his
wife, the children, the whole family.

00:21:38.331 --> 00:21:41.657
That’s why a man can’t
afford to be disorientated.

00:21:41.657 --> 00:21:45.353
And he becomes disorientated
when he doesn’t listen to God.

00:21:45.353 --> 00:21:50.158
Because then you’re just lashing out and
going wherever a hundred other voices

00:21:50.158 --> 00:21:55.332
tell you: the family says one thing,
the wife another, the kids another, the

00:21:55.332 --> 00:21:57.919
boss another, this, that, and the rest.

00:21:57.919 --> 00:21:58.379
No.

00:21:58.379 --> 00:22:01.599
Decide who you’re going to listen to.

00:22:01.599 --> 00:22:04.358
Entrust your life to God first.

00:22:04.358 --> 00:22:09.877
You’ve got husbands, you’ve got men
who are constantly praying to God

00:22:09.877 --> 00:22:12.637
for their wife, for their children.

00:22:12.637 --> 00:22:14.936
Mate, pray for yourself first.

00:22:14.936 --> 00:22:16.776
Because you’re the locomotive.

00:22:16.776 --> 00:22:18.156
You’re the locomotive.

00:22:18.156 --> 00:22:20.915
And you women too—stop criticising men.

00:22:20.915 --> 00:22:25.515
Better to pray a novena
to a saint for him.

00:22:25.515 --> 00:22:25.975
Why?

00:22:25.975 --> 00:22:31.736
That’s why I say it’s really important:
if the head of the family rushes in

00:22:31.736 --> 00:22:33.657
blindly, everyone rushes in blindly.

00:22:33.657 --> 00:22:34.809
General chaos follows.

00:22:34.809 --> 00:22:39.803
Because if we started picking families
apart again, we’d end up poking our

00:22:39.803 --> 00:22:41.723
noses into other people’s business.

00:22:41.723 --> 00:22:45.181
But I believe you don’t need to be afraid.

00:22:45.181 --> 00:22:50.174
Look at how many challenges Joseph
and Mary, as the Holy Family, had:

00:22:50.174 --> 00:22:53.631
uncertainty, fear, enemies, constantly
being uprooted and moved about.

00:22:53.631 --> 00:22:58.625
Just imagine it — with a small child
you’re going, walking, travelling; as many

00:22:58.625 --> 00:23:00.929
challenges as you could possibly want.

00:23:00.990 --> 00:23:03.587
How immense must that
trust in God have been?

00:23:03.587 --> 00:23:05.030
And what about us today?

00:23:05.030 --> 00:23:06.762
We want everything to be certain.

00:23:06.762 --> 00:23:11.092
You won’t get married, you won’t do this,
you won’t move out from your parents

00:23:11.092 --> 00:23:13.112
because you don’t know how you’ll manage.

00:23:13.112 --> 00:23:15.999
You won’t marry because you
don’t know what’s coming, you

00:23:15.999 --> 00:23:19.751
haven’t got a secure future, you
haven’t bought a house or a car.

00:23:19.751 --> 00:23:23.215
We want everything guaranteed — but where,
then, is our communication with God?

00:23:23.215 --> 00:23:28.313
Yesterday I preached about the word that
kills you, and why you don’t do many good

00:23:28.313 --> 00:23:30.226
things – and that word is hesitation.

00:23:30.226 --> 00:23:33.094
And when we hesitate, we
stop doing God’s will.

00:23:33.094 --> 00:23:37.555
Because if God knows something is
good for you, and he urges you on…

00:23:37.555 --> 00:23:42.017
Now imagine this: the angel of the
Lord comes to Joseph and says, “Get

00:23:42.017 --> 00:23:46.478
up, take Mary…” and Joseph says, “Oh
dear, I need a bit more information.

00:23:46.478 --> 00:23:49.028
Come back a few more times, will you?

00:23:49.028 --> 00:23:53.490
So I can work out how and what,
and get my head round it.”

00:23:55.130 --> 00:23:57.386
Imagine if he had acted like that.

00:23:57.386 --> 00:23:59.319
And we hesitate—what do we do?

00:23:59.319 --> 00:24:03.831
We don’t have faith and trust in God;
instead we gather information to make

00:24:03.831 --> 00:24:07.699
ourselves feel safer, to calculate as
securely as possible whether we’re going

00:24:07.699 --> 00:24:09.955
to risk anything, and what might happen.

00:24:09.955 --> 00:24:13.500
And that hesitation—we can even
dress it up as something pious.

00:24:13.500 --> 00:24:18.012
Then we say it’s sensible to think
it through, that we need to look

00:24:18.012 --> 00:24:21.879
at it wisely, but in fact what’s
hiding behind it is unbelief.

00:24:21.879 --> 00:24:26.847
And every postponement, every hesitation
in response to God’s prompting, is

00:24:26.847 --> 00:24:29.105
you showing disobedience to God.

00:24:29.105 --> 00:24:34.523
And you can see here, through this
whole homily and the interpretation

00:24:34.523 --> 00:24:39.491
of these readings tonight, just
how important obedience to God was.

00:24:39.491 --> 00:24:44.458
Because you will never gain
clarity while you sit and wait.

00:24:44.458 --> 00:24:47.167
Nor will God ever give it.

00:24:47.167 --> 00:24:52.135
Look—Saint Joseph is an example: he
didn’t have complete clarity either.

00:24:52.135 --> 00:24:54.447
And last night I was listing other saints.

00:24:54.447 --> 00:24:55.892
They didn’t have it either.

00:24:55.892 --> 00:24:59.939
Moses didn’t have complete clarity;
it was simply, “Get up and set off for

00:24:59.939 --> 00:25:03.985
the Promised Land.” And Saint Paul—when
Jesus said to him, “Come out onto the

00:25:03.985 --> 00:25:08.610
water, walk on the water towards me,” he
didn’t say, “Wait, I might sink; I’m not

00:25:08.610 --> 00:25:13.235
completely sure I can walk.” So what is
it that happens in God’s way of teaching?

00:25:13.235 --> 00:25:18.085
We gain certainty and clarity
only once we set off on the path.

00:25:18.085 --> 00:25:19.205
On the path.

00:25:19.205 --> 00:25:21.070
That’s why I’m encouraging you.

00:25:21.070 --> 00:25:25.175
It’s better to take the risk,
because you’re all afraid of

00:25:25.175 --> 00:25:27.041
making a mistake, of risking.

00:25:27.041 --> 00:25:32.638
And believe me, it’s a lesser sin
to take a risk and get it wrong

00:25:32.638 --> 00:25:34.877
than to hesitate and do nothing.

00:25:34.877 --> 00:25:40.101
Because why, in the Gospel, did
they go after the one who received a

00:25:40.101 --> 00:25:42.340
single talent—what sin did he commit?

00:25:42.340 --> 00:25:43.565
He didn’t do anything.

00:25:43.565 --> 00:25:47.548
That’s what he did wrong: he hid
the talent he was given, buried

00:25:47.548 --> 00:25:49.387
it, and did nothing with it.

00:25:49.387 --> 00:25:54.596
And while you hesitate, a day goes by,
a month goes by, three go by, and we

00:25:54.596 --> 00:25:57.966
never make certain decisions—yet God
has destined you for the struggle.

00:25:57.966 --> 00:26:01.337
God has given you a task,
to entrust something to you.

00:26:01.337 --> 00:26:06.240
If he entrusted his Son to Joseph, if
he entrusted Mary to Joseph to care for…

00:26:06.405 --> 00:26:11.794
I believe that God has given each and
every one of us a mission, a person,

00:26:11.794 --> 00:26:14.826
a role in life; He has faith in us.

00:26:14.826 --> 00:26:16.510
That’s why we mustn’t hesitate.

00:26:16.510 --> 00:26:20.216
That’s why Saint Joseph is
an example for us: he didn’t

00:26:20.216 --> 00:26:21.563
have everything crystal clear.

00:26:21.563 --> 00:26:22.237
Get going.

00:26:22.237 --> 00:26:26.279
And let’s stop, I’m saying, hiding
behind those words with all those…

00:26:26.279 --> 00:26:31.332
patterns, excuses: “I think it’s wise
to wait a bit, I think it’s wise to

00:26:31.332 --> 00:26:36.385
think it through, I don’t think I
should rush into it, I don’t think I’m

00:26:36.385 --> 00:26:39.080
a hundred per cent sure,” and so on.

00:26:39.600 --> 00:26:43.565
So, imagine this: from a single sentence
Joseph has to know this and that.

00:26:43.565 --> 00:26:47.813
When someone comes to you from heaven
to tell you, and now the angel says,

00:26:47.813 --> 00:26:49.796
“You will see Jesus,” and so on.

00:26:49.796 --> 00:26:53.761
But how are you to bring him up,
care for him, and everything else?

00:26:53.761 --> 00:26:58.293
Yet from Joseph’s example we see that
if you are God’s man, if you listen to

00:26:58.293 --> 00:27:00.275
Him, God will make what’s needed happen.

00:27:00.275 --> 00:27:04.807
And I find it quite fitting that at
Christmas we spend a bit more time with

00:27:04.807 --> 00:27:09.339
this theme of the Holy Family; I’ve always
found it close to my heart, because that’s

00:27:09.339 --> 00:27:11.604
genuinely how it is in the spiritual life.

00:27:12.945 --> 00:27:15.344
They always escaped a dangerous
situation—like people say—by

00:27:15.344 --> 00:27:16.844
the skin of their teeth.

00:27:16.844 --> 00:27:20.143
But it wasn’t really that they
escaped; it was God’s providence.

00:27:20.143 --> 00:27:24.342
It never happened to them that, say,
when they wanted to kill all the

00:27:24.342 --> 00:27:28.241
little children, the angel would come:
“Take the child, run, so they don’t…”

00:27:28.241 --> 00:27:32.440
So everything was always by a hair’s
breadth. And we too, if we’re Christian

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:34.540
believers, have to get used to that.

00:27:34.540 --> 00:27:37.045
If we belong to God, we have trust.

00:27:37.045 --> 00:27:40.802
Believe me, God won’t sort things
out months in advance, or days

00:27:40.802 --> 00:27:42.994
in advance, just so we feel safe.

00:27:42.994 --> 00:27:45.186
It’ll always be right on the edge.

00:27:45.186 --> 00:27:46.752
Always right on the edge.

00:27:46.752 --> 00:27:50.196
I’ve been shocked more than once
by God’s intervention: when you

00:27:50.196 --> 00:27:53.328
think everything’s closed off, that
something’s impossible to sort out.

00:27:53.328 --> 00:27:58.024
And then, all of a sudden, God sorts
it out at the very last moment.

00:27:58.024 --> 00:28:02.374
So, a bit of adventure, people – come
on, throw yourselves into it.

00:28:02.374 --> 00:28:06.723
Look, since I hadn’t prepared a
sermon, I asked the altar servers

00:28:06.723 --> 00:28:09.985
whether anyone had more experience
of St Joseph’s intercession.

00:28:09.985 --> 00:28:15.783
And one lad said he did, so please,
could you come up for a moment – just

00:28:15.783 --> 00:28:20.132
briefly to give your testimony – so
it’s not just me retelling it

00:28:20.132 --> 00:28:21.945
when he’s already here present.

00:28:26.564 --> 00:28:27.385
Go on, go on.

00:28:27.465 --> 00:28:30.809
Well, there you go — thank you, Marija.

00:28:30.809 --> 00:28:37.020
I believe many of you have been
praying the novena to Saint Joseph

00:28:37.020 --> 00:28:38.931
that’s just finished yesterday.

00:28:38.931 --> 00:28:46.098
So, over those nine weeks, I was sort
of praying the novena to Saint Joseph

00:28:46.098 --> 00:28:53.264
together with my girlfriend, so that I’d
get a job in construction — and today, on

00:28:53.264 --> 00:28:56.608
Saint Joseph’s Day, I signed the contract.

00:28:56.608 --> 00:28:58.520
So, just keep praying.

00:29:08.100 --> 00:29:11.745
You heard him say: fiancée,
job — so how could it not be

00:29:11.745 --> 00:29:13.264
worth praying to Saint Joseph?

00:29:13.264 --> 00:29:14.480
The man got everything.

